{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines the scope of services provided by the Promoter, but lacks clarity on liability for performance failures and potential disputes regarding compensation.",
  "operative_text": "Promoter to provide the following services to VNUE in accordance with the terms and conditions set forth in this agreement: A. VNUE hereby engages the Promoter as an Independent Contractor to secure contracts for VNUE with Thirty (30) music venues. B. The Promoter will provide certain skills, expertise, experience and abilities developed as global leader in the music and entertainment business over two decades. C. The Promoter will consult and work with the Directors and Officers of VNUE concerning matters relating to business development and other matters deemed necessary to perform the Promotion Services.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on liability for performance failures by the Promoter, which could lead to disputes regarding compensation and potential financial losses for VNUE.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["VNUE", "Promoter"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines the payment structure for the Promoter's services in securing contracts with music venues, including a combination of cash and VNUE common stock. It lacks clarity on how capital calls will be handled upon termination.",
  "operative_text": "For providing services as set forth herein, VNUE will compensate Promoter i) Two Thousand Five Hundred Dollars ($2,500.00) for each One (1) Year contract Promoter secures per venue and Five Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00) for each Two (2) Year contract Promoter secures per venue, with payment due to Promoter within Thirty (30) Days from the date on which each such contract is countersigned; and ii) through the issuance of VNUE common stock as set forth below, and for the purposes of Rule 144 such shares of stock shall be deemed to have fully earned by Promoter upon the date of each issuance of such stock certificates by VStock Transfer:   Three Million (3,000,000) shares of VNUE common stock shall be awarded to Promoter for performing Promotion Services as follows: ",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on how capital calls will be handled upon termination.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["VNUE"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines the reimbursement structure for expenses incurred by the operator, but lacks clarity on how disputes regarding costs will be handled.",
  "operative_text": "VNUE shall reimburse Promoter for expenses incurred by Promoter while performing the duties herein. Promoter shall deliver to VNUE an itemized accounting of expenses incurred on a weekly basis, and VNUE shall reimburse Promoter within Thirty (30) Days of receipt of such accounting.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "This clause lacks clarity on how disputes regarding costs will be handled. ",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["VNUE", "Promoter"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause addresses the non-operator's right to perform services and their obligation regarding confidential information, but it lacks detail on how disputes will be resolved or what constitutes 'confidential information'. This could lead to ambiguity and potential for conflict.",
  "operative_text": "Promoter affirms that Promoter is not restricted from providing services in this Agreement due to any agreement with any other person or entity. Promoter will not disclose to VNUE or use in its work any trade secrets, inventions or confidential information of any other person or entity which Promoter is not lawfully entitled to disclose or use.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks detail on how disputes regarding the non-operator's right to perform services and their obligations regarding confidential information will be resolved. This could lead to ambiguity and potential for conflict.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Promoter", "VNUE", "trade secrets", "inventions", "confidential information"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "non-operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause lacks clarity on how the joint venture's operations will be conducted, potentially leading to disputes and operational challenges.",
  "operative_text": "5. Place of Work. Promoter may perform the Promotion Services at such locations as Promoter may choose.\n",
